headline: Waymo valued at $126 billion in latest financing as robotaxis gather steam
summary: Alphabet unit Waymo said it had raised $16 billion in its latest fundraising round that valued ​the self-driving car startup at $126 billion, nearly tripling its valuation ‌in less than two years.  As one of the most sought-after applications of artificial ‌intelligence, leading autonomous vehicle companies are investing heavily in commercializing their technology, with a focus on safety and regulatory collaboration to gain market share.  The round was led by Dragoneer Investment Group, DST ⁠Global, and Sequoia Capital, ‌with additional investments from Mubadala Capital, Andreessen Horowitz and T. Rowe Price.
